{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-06-28T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Boneyard Beach within Hunting Island State Park, South Carolina, United States, the first thing you notice is the trees. Then comes the question: why are bleached trunks and exposed roots scattered across the sand like a scene paused midway through collapse? Since the 1980s, Hunting Island has experienced major beach erosion, with some of the highest rates along the US East Coast—reaching up to 9 metres per year in certain areas.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Driftwood on Boneyard Beach, Hunting Island, South Carolina, USA","Copyright":"© Frances/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hunting+Island&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260627_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach"},"Ssd":"20260627","Name":"BoneyardBeach","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5980184079","FullDateString":"27 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What does a parliament, a clock tower and a giant wheel have in common? They all stand beside the River Thames as if London had carefully staged its icons for dramatic effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The River Thames, London, England","Copyright":"© Daniel Lange/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=River+Thames&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260626_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer"},"Ssd":"20260626","Name":"ThamesSummer","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5725205310","FullDateString":"26 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Few squares in Belgium wear history as well as the Grand Place. The surrounding buildings, seen here, began as guild houses, each funded by a specific trade. Brewers, bakers, merchants and craftsmen treated architecture as language, translating work, status and rivalry into stone through reliefs, coats of arms and generous gold leaf. Styles meet without caution. Gothic verticals rise beside Baroque curves, while the Town Hall, older than its neighbours and unapologetically asymmetrical, holds the composition together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Buildings on Grand-Place Square in Brussels, Belgium","Copyright":"© Vladislav Zolotov/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Place+Brussels&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260625_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace"},"Ssd":"20260625","Name":"GrandPlace","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9942052634","FullDateString":"25 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Zoom in on the small interaction that helps keep landscapes alive: a butterfly on a yellow flower, pausing for nectar. While it feeds, pollen dusts its body and hitches a ride to the next bloom—one of the quiet ways flowering plants reproduce. Pollinators are not only bees. Butterflies, birds, bats, beetles and many other animals help move pollen, supporting wild plants and many of the fruits and vegetables people eat.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_ROW9877719219_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_ROW9877719219_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Butterfly pollinating on yellow flower","Copyright":"© lzh/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Butterfly&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260624_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin"},"Ssd":"20260624","Name":"BFPollin","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9877719219","FullDateString":"24 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Mount Fuji, Japan's highest mountain, rises to 3,776 metres on Honshu Island, about 97 kilometres southwest of Tokyo. Its near-perfect cone is a volcano—dormant since its last eruption in December 1707 yet still classed as active. That last major event is known as the Hōei eruption. It blasted ash and other tephra across eastern Japan, reaching Edo (today's Tokyo). Beyond geology, Fuji has long been treated as a sacred landscape and a destination for pilgrimage climbs, reflecting how nature, religion and daily life overlap in Japan. That enduring cultural appeal is one reason it was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2013 as 'a sacred place and source of artistic inspiration.' Fuji is famously visible from far away on clear days but never guaranteed—clouds can hide it in minutes. Whether you hike it or just catch a glimpse from a train window, it still feels like Japan's signature on the horizon.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_ROW9816660784_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_ROW9816660784_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mount Fuji on Honshu Island, Japan","Copyright":"© phutthiseth thongtae/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mount+Fuji&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260623_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan"},"Ssd":"20260623","Name":"Fujisan","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9816660784","FullDateString":"23 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Rainforests aren't just dots on the map. They thrive across the tropics and beyond, yet cover only about 6% of Earth's surface. Quinault, in Olympic National Park in Washington state, is a primeval temperate rainforest on the Olympic Peninsula, where Pacific moisture creates ideal conditions for dense growth. Rain and drifting fog keep the forest thriving, turning branches, trunks and even fallen logs into living surfaces.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_ROW9752257605_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_ROW9752257605_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Quinault rainforest, Olympic National Park, Washington state, United States","Copyright":"© Chris Moore/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Rainforest+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260622_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns"},"Ssd":"20260622","Name":"QuinaultFerns","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9752257605","FullDateString":"22 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Above the Tarn Valley, the Millau Viaduct seems to brush the sky. At 343 metres, its highest pylons rise taller than the Eiffel Tower. At dawn, light mist often drifts between the hills of the Larzac plateau and Aveyron, wrapping steel and concrete in an almost unreal softness. From some viewpoints, the bridge can appear to float above the clouds rather than standing upon them.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MillauViaductFrance_ROW0201721820_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MillauViaductFrance_ROW0201721820_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Millau Viaduct, France","Copyright":"© Sergi Reboredo/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260621_MillauViaductFrance\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Millau+Viaduct&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260621_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260621_MillauViaductFrance"},"Ssd":"20260621","Name":"MillauViaductFrance","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0201721820","FullDateString":"21 juni 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Tucked between vineyards and mountains, Kaysersberg is one of Alsace's most enchanting villages. Set along the Weiss River in northeastern France, it lies about 12 kilometres northwest of Colmar on the eastern slopes of the Vosges Mountains.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KaysersbergVillage_ROW7990431342_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KaysersbergVillage_ROW7990431342_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Kaysersberg, Alsace, France","Copyright":"© Federica Gentile/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260704_KaysersbergVillage\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kaysersberg&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260704_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260704_KaysersbergVillage"},"Ssd":"20260704","Name":"KaysersbergVillage","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7990431342","FullDateString":"4 juli 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Okayama Prefecture, when humid air settles over a stream, hotaru—Japan's fireflies—begin signalling. On warm, windless evenings, they often start glowing about two hours after sunset under favourable conditions, inviting silence beside water.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FirefliesJapan_ROW7733016954_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FirefliesJapan_ROW7733016954_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Fireflies glowing above a stream, Okayama Prefecture, Japan","Copyright":"© tdub303/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260703_FirefliesJapan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Firefly+insect&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260703_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260703_FirefliesJapan"},"Ssd":"20260703","Name":"FirefliesJapan","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7733016954","FullDateString":"3 juli 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the Temple of Esna, south of Luxor, Egypt, visitors enter a vivid world devoted to Khnum, the ram-headed god believed to have moulded humanity from Nile clay. Built mainly during the Ptolemaic and Roman eras, the temple's surviving hall is supported by 24 towering columns, each carved with intricate reliefs and ritual texts honouring various deities.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TempleEsna_ROW7472405327_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TempleEsna_ROW7472405327_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Ceiling of the Temple of Esna, Egypt","Copyright":"© Nick Brundle Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260702_TempleEsna\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Temple+of+Esna+Egypt&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260702_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260702_TempleEsna"},"Ssd":"20260702","Name":"TempleEsna","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7472405327","FullDateString":"2 juli 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image takes us to Dungeon Provincial Park on the rugged coast of Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada, where nature tells a much older story. Atlantic waves carved a sea cave with two openings, gradually widening it until the roof gave way. What remains is a striking collapsed formation known as a 'gloup,' surrounded by steep cliffs and crashing surf.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Dungeon Provincial Park, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada","Copyright":"© Kaitlyn McLachlan/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Dungeon+Provincial+Park+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260701_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark"},"Ssd":"20260701","Name":"DungeonPark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7201602273","FullDateString":"1 juli 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As the sun sinks low in the Masai Mara National Reserve, the silhouettes of Masai giraffes rise against a blazing sky and open plains. Another day comes to an end in the reserve, which stretches across about 1,500 square kilometres in southwestern Kenya, bordering Tanzania's Serengeti National Park. It is a vast expanse, one of the world's greatest wildlife arenas. Rolling grasslands, scattered acacia trees and the life-giving Mara River set the stage for unforgettable encounters.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Giraffes at sunset in the Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© danm/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260630_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe"},"Ssd":"20260630","Name":"MasaiGiraffe","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6806132366","FullDateString":"30 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Beyond its postcard views, Bora Bora has a deeper story to tell. Its lagoon reflects how tropical islands evolve over time. Surrounded by shades of turquoise, this island in French Polynesia is home to one of the South Pacific's most celebrated lagoons, where coral reefs, volcanic peaks and ocean life exist side by side.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Bora Bora and its lagoon, South Pacific, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© Frederick Millett/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bora+Bora&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260629_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260629","Name":"BoraBoraLagoon","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6505126632","FullDateString":"29 juni 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"'Stick around' takes on a new meaning in the Sonoran Desert, where the saguaro cactus has mastered survival. With trunks and arms raised in all directions, this giant has become the American Southwest's mascot.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Saguaro cacti near Windgate Pass, McDowell Range, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Eric Mischke/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Saguaro+cactus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260628_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun"},"Ssd":"20260628","Name":"SaguaroSun","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6246109819","FullDateString":"28 juni 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Dagens bild","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Mer information","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donera nu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Snabbfakta:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Nyligen använda startsidebilder","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Startsidebild {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Denna dag i historien","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Den här dagen i {0} {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Dela dagens Bing-star